{
  "texts": [
    "A long-only portfolio is one with all asset weights nonnegative, i.e., w ≥ 0 (elementwise).",
    "A portfolio with c = 0, i.e., no cash holdings, is called fully invested.",
    "In such a portfolio we have 1 T w = 1, i.e., the total asset weight is one.",
    "As another example, a cash-neutral portfolio is one with c = 1.",
    "For a cash-neutral portfolio we have 1 T w = 0, i.e., the total (net) asset weight is zero."
  ]
}